content.description:
This line climbs the beautiful splitter dihedral.  Some of the best jams in the Ozarks are found at the start of this climb.  Climb through tight hands, offwidth, a couple of tiny roofs, and more to finish on a large ledge to your right. 

  Watch out for the cactus guarding the ledge.
content.protection:
Single rack to #5 c4.  Depending on comfort one could use doubles from .75-2 c4 

  We left 2 nuts and a sling with a quick link for the anchor
content.location: Route is located in an obvious dihedral.  It is above a house sized boulder that can be seen from road during the fall and winter.

content.description:
A long bluff line with little development.  The rock quality is varied but overall is decent.  Lacks in height and steepness compared to other areas of rock.  The bluff has a plethora of boulders, slab sections, vertical walls, and cracks.   

  There are no established trails so it will be a bushwhacking adventure.
